      "index": 0,
      "text": "write out \u0027SignedDataSurvivesInList disabled (pending signature rework)\u0027",
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "indent": 0,
      "comment": "DISABLED \u2014 verify-through-a-list doesn\u0027t yet handle a signed Data that is correctly\npreserved AS a Data on round-trip (it ends up hashing a Data wrapping a Data, so the\nrehash differs from the signed hash). Re-enable when signing is reworked to wrap the\ndata in a signature object instead of hanging a Signature off Data.\n- sign \u0022hello world\u0022, write to %signed%\n- add %signed% to %list%\n- verify %list[0]%, write to %ok%\n- assert %ok% equals true",
